In a phone call, President Biden discussed the Build Back Better Act and the Bipartisan Infrastructure Deal with Speaker Pelosi and Leader Schumer. They talked about reaching out to Democratic members and the progress made to fulfill promises for the middle class. They also discussed avoiding a breach of the United States' full faith and credit due to Republican obstruction. They agreed to continue working on the legislation that aligns with the President's vision for creating jobs and making investments in families. They will coordinate closely in the coming days.